{"article_id":"Oxjd3cacIugdrVsW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner , on the heels of an election","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that left the balance of power in Washington unchanged ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"made the first move","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"in crafting the framework for a deal","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"to potentially avert the so-called `` fiscal cliff . ''","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The speaker , on a phone call with Republicans , said","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"he 'd like a `` bridge '' measure","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"to get negotiators past the looming year-end deadline","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"that would ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"if left un-addressed ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"trigger automatic spending cuts and tax hikes ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"people familiar with the call told Fox News .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Separately , Boehner told reporters","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"he wants to then see `` major solutions '' in 2013","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"`` that begin to solve the problem . ''","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Republicans are willing to accept `` new revenue , ''","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"while indicating","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that does n't mean higher tax rates .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Rather , Boehner said","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"his party is willing to bring in more revenue","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"by closing loopholes","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and ending certain deductions through comprehensive tax reform","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"-- but only if Democrats are willing to deal ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"by making serious spending cuts","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and putting entitlements on the table .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"`` In order to garner Republican support for new revenues ,","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"the president must be willing to reduce spending and shore up the entitlement programs","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that are the primary drivers of our debt . ''","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"The push","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"to craft a short-term bill ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"though ,","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"could end up creating yet another future deadline","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"that lawmakers wait until the eleventh hour","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"to address .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"Short-term measures have become a go-to solution for a gridlocked Congress","depth":4},{"id":36,"text":"-- with the body repeatedly passing budget bills","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"known as `` continuing resolutions ''","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"in lieu of a full-scale budget .","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"The need for renewed fiscal talks grew in urgency","depth":4},{"id":40,"text":"after Tuesday 's elections did little to change the dynamic in Washington ,","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"with Democrats holding on to the White House and Senate","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"and Republicans keeping control of the House .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"A deal has so far been held up by a central sticking point","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"-- whether to extend all the Bush-era tax rates ,","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"or let them lapse for those","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"making $ 250,000 and up .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Both sides have pledged in the aftermath of the election to work together ,","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"but for the past two years bipartisan cooperation has been virtually non-existent .","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"Boehner , in the Republican House leaders ' call with members , expressed concern","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"about getting major legislation passed in a lame-duck session ,","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"making a short-term measure more reasonable","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"until the new Congress is sworn in .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"However , he also spoke to the Republicans ' broader agenda in comments to reporters Wednesday afternoon ,","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"new revenue is on the table","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"as long as it comes through tax loophole reform , not rate hikes .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"House Majority Leader Eric Cantor also spoke out Wednesday on Republicans ' goals for the new session ,","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"saying in a letter to House Republicans","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"though the party and the president do n't agree on many issues ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"it was their duty to come together","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"and work for the American people .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"`` Our task is to legislate","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"based on our principles","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"and forge the compromise","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"that will be necessary","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"to get our nation back on track , ''","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"the letter said .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"However , he also said","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"that the GOP would stick to their principles","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"when dealing with the `` fiscal cliff , ''","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"and would push for a fundamental reform of the tax code","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"rather than increasing taxes .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"In the Senate , Majority Leader Harry Reid said Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"that `` we need to start working together , a lot .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Gridlock is not the solution . ''","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Even so , he disputed Boehner 's contention","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that the public does n't support a tax increase ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"the election was a `` mandate ...","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"that the richest of the rich have to help a little bit . ''","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"`` I 'm going to do everything within my power","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"to be as conciliatory","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"as possible .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"I want to work together ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"but I want everyone to also understand ,","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"you ca n't push us around , ''","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"Reid said ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"adding :","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"`` I think","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"we should just roll up our sleeves","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"and get it done . ''","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"The Bush-era tax rates are just one of a handful of problems","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"facing President Obama and the lame-duck Congress .","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"Obama and the Democrats want to let the lower rates expire for top income earners ,","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"while Republicans want to preserve the existing rates for everyone .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"If they ca n't compromise ,","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"all tax rates will increase .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"Separately , steep automatic cuts to defense and social spending are set to kick in automatically in January , something","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"both sides say","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"they do n't want","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"even though they agreed to the cuts in 2011 as an incentive","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"to get negotiators to strike a long-term deficit-reduction deal .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"That deal never came ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"leaving the country at risk of federal cuts","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"that some fear","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"could bring the country back into a recession .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":215,"left":146,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":136,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":119,"right":135,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":112,